AECI, Anglo American, Aquarius, Northam: South Africa Stock Market Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-25T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/aeci-anglo-american-aquarius-northam-south-africa-stock-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 49.54, or 0.2
percent, to 32,065.84 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, after
declining 0.8 percent last week.  AECI Ltd. (AFE)  : The explosives and chemicals company
 publishes first-half earnings . Shares of the company fell 0.6
percent to 84.50 rand.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  :  De Beers , the world’s biggest
diamond producer, in which Anglo American has a 45 percent
stake, publishes first-half earnings. Shares in Anglo dropped
0.3 percent to 334.36 rand.  Aquarius Platinum Ltd. (AQP)  : The world’s fourth-largest
producer of the metal  reports fourth-quarter results . The stock
declined 1.6 percent to 34 rand.  Northam Platinum Ltd. (NHM)  : The operator of the world’s
deepest platinum mine resumes wage talks with the  National Union
of Mineworkers . Shares in the company increased 1.9 percent to
39.72 rand.  Santova Logistics Ltd. (SNV)  : The clearing agent for
importers and exporters holds its annual general meeting. The
stock was unchanged at 6 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
